    "plan_content": "Here's the plan I've built after thoroughly exploring the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: Ollama Model Rename Feature\n\n**4 files to change, 7 discrete edits** — all additive, nothing removed.\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- `getExistingName()` (routes.go:1031) is just a **case-normalizer** against existing manifests — it never fails for a missing model. The real existence check always comes from `manifest.ParseNamedManifest()`.\n- `CopyModel()` (images.go:397) requires fully qualified names and returns `os.ErrNotExist` when the source manifest file is missing — this is the 404 signal.\n- `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg` (not the inline format string used by `CopyHandler`) is the correct constant to use for invalid name errors, matching the pattern in `create.go` and `writeModelRefParseError`.\n\n### The 7 edits\n\n| # | File | What |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest{Source, Destination}` struct after `CopyRequest` |\n| 2 | `api/client.go` | `Rename()` method using `c.do(POST, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)` |\n| 3 | `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler`: validate → check dst doesn't exist (409) → `CopyModel` → `m.Remove()` + `m.RemoveLayers()` → 200 |\n| 4 | `server/routes.go` | Register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy` |\n| 5 | `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` func using `client.Rename()`, prints `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"` |\n| 6 | `cmd/cmd.go` | `renameCmd` cobra command with `ExactArgs(2)` + `checkServerHeartbeat` |\n| 7 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `renameCmd` after `copyCmd` in `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` |",
